{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/addPoint(id:position:weightScale:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/arePointsConnected(id:toId:bidirectional:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/clear()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/connectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/disconnectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getAvailablePointId()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getClosestPoint(toPosition:includeDisabled:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getClosestPositionInSegment(toPosition:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getIdPath(fromId:toId:allowPartialPath:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointCapacity()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointConnections(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointCount()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointIds()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointPath(fromId:toId:allowPartialPath:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointPosition(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointWeightScale(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/hasPoint(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/isPointDisabled(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/removePoint(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/reserveSpace(numNodes:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/setPointDisabled(id:disabled:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/setPointPosition(id:position:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/setPointWeightScale(id:weightScale:)"],"title":"Instance Methods","generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/godotClassName"],"generated":true,"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/astar3d"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RefCounted"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AStar3D","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A* (A star) is a computer algorithm used in pathfinding and graph traversal, the process of plotting short paths among vertices (points), passing through a given set of edges (segments). It enjoys widespread use due to its performance and accuracy. Godot’s A* implementation uses points in 3D space and Euclidean distances by default."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You must add points manually with "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/addPoint(id:position:weightScale:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" and create segments manually with ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/connectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)"},{"type":"text","text":". Once done, you can test if there is a path between two points with the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/arePointsConnected(id:toId:bidirectional:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" function, get a path containing indices by ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getIdPath(fromId:toId:allowPartialPath:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", or one containing actual coordinates with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointPath(fromId:toId:allowPartialPath:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is also possible to use non-Euclidean distances. To do so, create a class that extends ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D"},{"type":"text","text":" and override methods "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". Both take two indices and return a length, as is shown in the following example."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" should return a lower bound of the distance, i.e. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_estimate_cost(u, v) <= _compute_cost(u, v)"},{"text":". This serves as a hint to the algorithm because the custom ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)"},{"text":" might be computation-heavy. If this is not the case, make ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)"},{"text":" return the same value as ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to provide the algorithm with the most accurate information."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the default "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)"},{"text":" methods are used, or if the supplied ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method returns a lower bound of the cost, then the paths returned by A* will be the lowest-cost paths. Here, the cost of a path equals the sum of the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" results of all segments in the path multiplied by the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"weight_scale"},{"type":"text","text":"s of the endpoints of the respective segments. If the default methods are used and the "},{"code":"weight_scale","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s of all points are set to ","type":"text"},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then this equals the sum of Euclidean distances of all segments in the path.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AStar3D","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","title":"AStar3D","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot7AStar3DC","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AStar3D","kind":"identifier"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"An implementation of A* for finding the shortest path between two vertices on a connected graph in 3D space.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/AStar3D/disconnectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Deletes the segment between the given points. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bidirectional"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":", only movement from ","type":"text"},{"code":"id","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"toId"},{"text":" is prevented, and a unidirectional segment possibly remains.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/disconnectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)","title":"disconnectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/astar3d\/disconnectpoints(id:toid:bidirectional:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"disconnectPoints"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"id","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"toId","kind":"externalParam"}